org.mitre.tdp.boogie

Enum TransitionType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TransitionType>
      • org.mitre.tdp.boogie.TransitionType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TransitionType>

    public enum TransitionType
extends java.lang.Enum<TransitionType>
    High-level classification of the type of transition implementing the Transition interface. This breakdown is leveraged in the route expansion logic.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      APPROACH
      Common type for all approach procedure transitions.
      COMMON
      Indicates this is the shared portion of the SID or STAR through which all traffic flying the procedure travels.
      ENROUTE
      Indicates this transition is mean't to take aircraft from/to the enroute portion of the flight plan into/out of the common portion of the STAR or SID.
      MISSED
      If there are tags for missed approach transitions as part of the ProcedureType.APPROACH use this tag can be used and they will be zipped on the ends of the primary approach transitions.
      RUNWAY
      Indicates the transition is mean't to support service either to or from a runway at a particular airport.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ENROUTE

        public static final TransitionType ENROUTE
        Indicates this transition is mean't to take aircraft from/to the enroute portion of the flight plan into/out of the common portion of the STAR or SID. Along transitions of this type is frequently when events like holding occur.

      • COMMON

        public static final TransitionType COMMON
        Indicates this is the shared portion of the SID or STAR through which all traffic flying the procedure travels.

      • RUNWAY

        public static final TransitionType RUNWAY
        Indicates the transition is mean't to support service either to or from a runway at a particular airport. For SIDs typically this is a sequence of CA and VI type legs, for STARs this is really to get the aircraft to its preferred ProcedureType.APPROACH for its target runway.

      • APPROACH

        public static final TransitionType APPROACH
        Common type for all approach procedure transitions.

      • MISSED

        public static final TransitionType MISSED
        If there are tags for missed approach transitions as part of the ProcedureType.APPROACH use this tag can be used and they will be zipped on the ends of the primary approach transitions. If missed approaches aren't a concern then just tag these as APPROACH, there is generally little affect on the algorithms results.
